## Plan-artifact canonical contract

The full schema, per-section shapes, per-list caps, and string-length tiers for the plan artifact live in `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md`. The bullets below point at the matching format-doc section for the topic that previously had an inlined pointer in this template:

- Plan size limits → `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Plan size limits` (4 MB hard cap, per-list caps, `PlanArtifactSizeError` before Pydantic).
- Planning quality → `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Planning quality guidance` (analysis-ready criteria, exact verification, acceptance criteria, evidence, and risk coverage).
- Cycle guard → `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md` §`Cycle guard` (`depends_on` DAG contract; diamond-shaped DAGs accepted).

Native file and shell tools are disabled in this brokered fallback; native orchestration tools remain enabled. Use the plan tools exactly as named below. Step mutation tools echo the new step number(s), the `depends_on` reindex map, and the AC ids whose `satisfied_by_steps` were rewritten.

- Use {{SUBMIT_PLAN_SECTION_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to stage `summary`, `skills_mcp`, `steps`, `critical_files`, `risks_mitigations`, and `verification_strategy`. Stage `design` for non-trivial plans so acceptance criteria, testability, drift detection, and refactor strategy are explicit before finalize.
- Use {{SUBMIT_PLAN_SECTIONS_TOOL_REFERENCE}} only when every entry already contains complete, analysis-ready section content.
- Use {{VALIDATE_PLAN_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to dry-run the cross-section validator before finalize and {{GET_PLAN_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} to inspect the staged draft if validation fails.
- Use {{FINALIZE_PLAN_TOOL_REFERENCE}} once all required sections are staged, and {{DISCARD_PLAN_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} only to throw the draft away.
